Olaide Oyelude, Katsina eighteen-year-old Abdullahi Lawal of Nasarawa village in the Dandume Local Government Area of Katsina State has been arrested by the police for being in possession of 46 wraps of dried leaves suspected to be Indian hemp. Lawal was arrested on September 13, 2019, when the police raided criminal hideouts in the area. He was said to have confessed to the crime. The spokesman for the Katsina State Police Command, SP Gambo Isah, confirmed the development on Wednesday, adding that Lawal would be prosecuted. The command also recovered an ash Toyota Highlander SUV, 2008 model, with Abuja number plate, RBC 434 JA. The vehicle was reportedly snatched from its owner in Zaria, Kaduna State. Isah said, “On September 17, 2019, around 3.30am, based on a tip-off, a patrol team attached to the Danja Division was alerted that armed robbers attacked the residence of one Mr Emmanuel Ayni of the Graceland Quarter, Zaria, Kaduna State, and robbed him of his ash Toyota Highlander SUV, 2008 model, with number plate RBC 434 JA, and were coming towards Katsina State.” Copyright PUNCH.
